CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 4, 1950, pg. 32, reads: "Given Car At Diamond Market - Mrs. Marie Diesner, 5424 Columbo Street, and her husband, Joseph, are shown at the Diamond Market, Diamond and Market Streets, Downtown, shortly after she was given the automobile shown above. Mrs. Diesner has purchased meat from the New Diamond Market for the past fifteen years, in fact, ever since she married. She was two children, Joseph, 8, and Patricia, 12.  Her husband is employed by Gulf Oil Research Department. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Three men wearing light colored jackets surrounding Joseph Diesner and Marie Diesner in front of Plymouth DeLuxe car, with New Diamond Market in background
